    public class MessageHandler

      • isCommand

        public boolean isCommand(net.dv8tion.jda.core.entities.Message msg)
        Returns if a given message can be parsed into a BotCommand. Automatically checks for the command prefix settings within BotSettings.
        Parameters:
        msg - - Discord Message instance to check.
        Returns:
        If the specified message is parseable as a command.

      • registerCommand

        public boolean registerCommand(BotCommand newCmd)
        Registers a command to this MessageHandler. Commands must be registered before they will be able to be exectued by users and detected by help commands.
        Parameters:
        newCmd - - Command to be registered
        Returns:
        If the command was successfully added, i.e. ArrayList.add(Object)

      • unregisterCommand

        public boolean unregisterCommand(BotCommand newCmd)
        Unregisters a command in this MessageHandler. Once removed, users can no longer use the command as the handler will not be able to access the command.
        Parameters:
        newCmd - - Command to be unregistered.
        Returns:
        If the command was successfully removed, i.e. ArrayList.remove(Object)

      • addReactionHandler

        public void addReactionHandler(long messageid,
                               ReactionHandler handler)
        Assigns a ReactionHandler to the specified message id. If MessageReactions are added to the specified message, the ReactionHandler's handleReaction method will be called automatically.
        Parameters:
        messageid - - Message ID to listen for reaction events.
        handler - - ReactionHandler to be assigned.

      • removeReactionHandler

        public void removeReactionHandler(long messageId)

        Parameters:
        messageId - - Message ID to remove ReactionHandlers from.
